def execute_command(system, tools):

    activation_list, image_list = tools.dataset_exemplars(system)

    summarization = tools.summarize_images(image_list)

def execute_command(system, tools):
    # Test the neuron's response to different animal faces
    prompts_animal_faces = [
        "the face of a cat",
        "the face of a dog",
        "the face of a lion",
        "the face of a frog",
        "the face of a tiger"
    ]
    images_animal_faces = tools.text2image(prompts_animal_faces)
    activation_list_faces, activation_map_list_faces = system.call_neuron(images_animal_faces)
    
    # Test the neuron's response specifically to animal noses or muzzles
    prompts_animal_noses = [
        "close-up view of a cat's nose",
        "close-up view of a dog's nose",
        "close-up view of a lion's nose",
        "close-up view of a frog's nose",
        "close-up view of a tiger's nose"
    ]
    images_animal_noses = tools.text2image(prompts_animal_noses)
    activation_list_noses, activation_map_list_noses = system.call_neuron(images_animal_noses)
    
    # Test the neuron's response to textural patterns like fur or skin
    prompts_textures = [
        "a patch of spotted fur",
        "a smooth patch of skin",
        "a striped tiger fur texture"
    ]
    images_textures = tools.text2image(prompts_textures)
    activation_list_textures, activation_map_list_textures = system.call_neuron(images_textures)
    
    # Save experiment results
    tools.save_experiment_log(
        activation_list_faces + activation_list_noses + activation_list_textures,
        activation_map_list_faces + activation_map_list_noses + activation_map_list_textures,
        prompts_animal_faces + prompts_animal_noses + prompts_textures,
        "Testing responses to animal faces, noses, and textural patterns"
    )
```

def execute_command(system, tools):
    # Test the neuron's response to changes in the structure of an animal face by manipulating a high-activation image
    # Here, we select "the face of a tiger" for editing since it resulted in high activation 
    prompt_tiger_face = ["the face of a tiger"]
    edits_structure = [
        "with larger eyes",
        "with no whiskers",
        "with a shorter muzzle",
        "with a different fur pattern"
    ]
    
    images_structure, prompts_structure = tools.edit_images(prompt_tiger_face, edits_structure)
    activation_list_structure, activation_map_list_structure = system.call_neuron(images_structure)
    
    # Test if varying texture independent of animal faces affects activation
    prompts_textures_independent = [
        "a rough surface with spots like a leopard",
        "a furry surface with stripes like a tiger",
        "a smooth surface like a frog's skin"
    ]
    
    images_textures_independent = tools.text2image(prompts_textures_independent)
    activation_list_textures_independent, activation_map_list_textures_independent = system.call_neuron(images_textures_independent)

    # Save experiment results
    tools.save_experiment_log(
        activation_list_structure + activation_list_textures_independent,
        activation_map_list_structure + activation_map_list_textures_independent,
        prompts_structure + prompts_textures_independent,
        "Testing for the effect of structural changes to animal faces and independent texture patterns on neuron activation"
    )
```

def execute_command(system, tools):
    # Different animals in various contexts to refine Hypothesis 1 about animal faces
    prompts_different_animals = [
        "the face of an elephant in a savannah",
        "the face of a monkey in a jungle",
        "the face of a bear in a forest",
        "the face of a wolf in snow"
    ]
    
    images_different_animals = tools.text2image(prompts_different_animals)
    activation_list_different_animals, activation_map_list_different_animals = system.call_neuron(images_different_animals)
    
    # Apply additional edits to a tiger face to refine Hypothesis 2 about noses and muzzles
    prompt_tiger_face = ["the face of a tiger"]
    edits_features = [
        "remove the tiger's fur",
        "change the tiger's nose to that of an elephant",
        "alter the tiger's face to be shorter, like a pug"
    ]
    
    images_features, prompts_features = tools.edit_images(prompt_tiger_face, edits_features)
    activation_list_features, activation_map_list_features = system.call_neuron(images_features)

    # Save experiment results
    tools.save_experiment_log(
        activation_list_different_animals + activation_list_features,
        activation_map_list_different_animals + activation_map_list_features,
        prompts_different_animals + prompts_features,
        "Refining hypotheses on animal faces and specific features contributing to higher neuron activation"
    )
```

def execute_command(system, tools):
    # Generate images of faces for other large predatory mammals to test Hypothesis 1
    prompts_predatory_mammals = [
        "the face of a cheetah with distinct fur patterns",
        "the face of a jaguar with close-up of its nose and mouth",
        "the face of a leopard with detailed fur texture"
    ]
    
    images_predatory_mammals = tools.text2image(prompts_predatory_mammals)
    activation_list_predatory_mammals, activation_map_list_predatory_mammals = system.call_neuron(images_predatory_mammals)
    
    # Generate images highlighting the nose and mouth area of large predatory mammals to test Hypothesis 2
    prompts_detailed_nose_mouth = [
        "the face of a tiger highlighting its nose and mouth",
        "the face of a lion with a close-up of its whisker area",
        "the face of a panther emphasizing the texture around its nose"
    ]
    
    images_detailed_nose_mouth = tools.text2image(prompts_detailed_nose_mouth)
    activation_list_detailed_nose_mouth, activation_map_list_detailed_nose_mouth = system.call_neuron(images_detailed_nose_mouth)

    # Save experiment results
    tools.save_experiment_log(
        activation_list_predatory_mammals + activation_list_detailed_nose_mouth,
        activation_map_list_predatory_mammals + activation_map_list_detailed_nose_mouth,
        prompts_predatory_mammals + prompts_detailed_nose_mouth,
        "Testing for high activations in faces of large predatory mammals emphasizing nose and mouth features"
    )
```
